every pair of adjacent vertices;\nsee `SimpleGraph.edgeSet` for the corresponding edge set.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/SimpleGraph/Basic.html#SimpleGraph","kind":"structure","line":86,"name":"SimpleGraph","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Combinatorics/SimpleGraph/Basic.lean#L86-L96"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/SimpleGraph/Basic.html#aesop_graph_nonterminal\"><span class=\"name\">aesop_graph_nonterminal</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A variant of `aesop_graph` which does not fail if it is unable to solve the goal.\nUse this only for exploration! Nonterminal Aesop is even worse than nonterminal `simp`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/SimpleGraph/Basic.html#aesop_graph_nonterminal","kind":"def","line":76,"name":"aesop_graph_nonterminal","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Combinatorics/SimpleGraph/Basic.lean#L76-L80"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/SimpleGraph/Basic.html#aesop_graph?\"><span class=\"name\">aesop_graph?</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Use `aesop_graph?` to pass along a `Try this` suggestion when using `aesop_graph`\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/SimpleGraph/Basic.html#aesop_graph?","kind":"def","line":66,"name":"aesop_graph?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Combinatorics/SimpleGraph/Basic.lean#L66-L70"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/SimpleGraph/Basic.html#aesop_graph\"><span class=\"name\">aesop_graph</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A variant of the `aesop` tactic for use in the graph library. Changes relative\nto standard `aesop`:\n\n- We use the `SimpleGraph` rule set in addition to the default rule sets.\n- We instruct Aesop's `intro` rule to unfold with `default` transparency.\n- We instruct Aesop to fail if it can't fully solve the goal. This allows us to\n  use `aesop_graph` for auto-params.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/SimpleGraph/Basic.html#aesop_graph","kind":"def","line":57,"name":"aesop_graph","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Combinatorics/SimpleGraph/Basic.lean#L57-L61"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Combinatorics.SimpleGraph.Init","Mathlib.Data.Finite.Prod","Mathlib.Data.Rel","Mathlib.Data.Set.Finite.Basic","Mathlib.Data.Sym.Sym2","Mathlib.Order.CompleteBooleanAlgebra"],"instances":[{"className":"Fintype","name":"instFintypeSimpleGraphOfDecidableEq","typeNames":["SimpleGraph"]},{"className":"Finite","name":"SimpleGraph.instFinite","typeNames":["SimpleGraph"]},{"className":"Decidable","name":"instDecidableRelAdjFromRelOfDecidableEq","typeNames":["SimpleGraph.Adj"]},{"className":"Std.Symm","name":"SimpleGraph.symm_adj","typeNames":[]},{"className":"LE","name":"SimpleGraph.instLE","typeNames":["SimpleGraph"]},{"className":"Max","name":"SimpleGraph.instMax","typeNames":["SimpleGraph"]},{"className":"Min","name":"SimpleGraph.instMin","typeNames":["SimpleGraph"]},{"className":"Compl","name":"SimpleGraph.instCompl","typeNames":["SimpleGraph"]}